article.headline: Against ASU, Kansas cures its offensive blues
article.story: TEMPE, Ariz. (AP) -- Preseason All-American Ike Diogu scored 20 of his 28 points in the second half to lead Arizona State to a 94-74 exhibition victory over Basketball Travelers on Monday night. Diogu, who also had 10 rebounds, shot 10-for-13 from the field and 7-for-7 at the foul line in his first play of the preseason. The sophomore forward sat out last week's exhibition game against the EA Sports All-Stars because if a right hip strain. Ed Williams led Basketball Travelers with 23 points. Arizona State opens its regular season Saturday at home against Arkansas-Little Rock.
